Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
add_connection...hbor_partition(25.10)  add_connection...hbor_partition(25.10)

Name
       add_connection_to_neighbor_partition  -  Adds  a  partition  pin on the
       abutted edge of unique abutting partitions to create a 2-partition  pin
       scenario for target pins

Syntax
       add_connection_to_neighbor_partition

       [-help]

       [-dictFile <file_name>]

       Adds  a partition pin on the abutted edge of unique abutting partitions
       to create a 2-partition pin scenario for target  pins.  This  helps  to
       avoid  floating  pins  on  abutted  edges. The add_connection_to_neigh-
       bor_partition command targets the following pins:

              * Input partition pins with tie definition and a GNC/UPF to  re-
                solve the tie net to a supply

              * Floating output partition pins

       Note:   The  target pins may or may not have any load/driver inside the
       partition.

       This command should be used after the pins have been assigned  for  the
       target  partition  and  tie  cells  have  been specified using the set-
       TieHiLoMode -cell command.

Parameters
       -dictFile <file_name>
              Specifies the name of the file in which the  TCL  dictionary  is
              written.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each add_connection_to_neighbor_partition  para-
              meter.  For a detailed description of the command and all of its
              parameters, use the man command:

              man add_connection_to_neighbor_partition

Example
              * The following command adds partition pins on  abutting  parti-
                tions  and  reports  the  number of new partition pins and tie
                cells in a table.

                add_connection_to_neighbor_partition

                -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                |    Type     | Total Pins | Pins placed in abutted edge | New
                partition pins added |

                -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                |   Tie-low   |           4  |                            4  |
                4 |

                |    Tie-hi     |           4  |                           4 |
                4 |

                | Floating(I) |          16  |                           16  |
                - |

                |  Floating(O)  |          16  |                          16 |
                16 |

                -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

